Warszewo  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Młynary, within Elbląg County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  south-west of Młynary,  north-east of Elbląg, and  north-west of the regional capital Olsztyn.
